    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-10-14T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-10-14T07:00:00-05:00" n="1017"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1017">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111/4127</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EMF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Egan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-14T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1916, 1 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 11.50 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>368. Your circular, October 10, 1 p. m.<note n="1" xml:id="d1017fn1">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_772">p. 772</ref>.</note>
                    Danish Government have issued no decrees or decisions concerning war submarines
                    except as contained in its law of December 20, 1912, the substance of which is
                    that war submarines shall be treated as other war vessels. The law follows
                    closely the, principles of the convention of The Hague. The question of merchant
                    submarines has not arisen and the Government is not willing to give a decision
                    until that question shall arise.</p>
                <p>This statement is practically the same as contained in the reply of the Danish
                    Government dated October 6 to the Allies’ collective note of August 27. 1 am
                    forwarding by mail a copy of note which, at the request of the Danish
                    Government, is to be treated as strictly confidential.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EMF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
